
There is still no official release of the SaX package.
Preliminary snapshots from the CVS can be downloaded at ...
Since the code is fairly unstable, at the moment we suggest to use
SaX through a scientific collaboration with our group (see CONTACTS).

TERMS OF USE.
Although users are not under any obligation in the spirit of the GNU General Public Licence,
we would appreciate the acknowledgment of the effort to produce
such codes in the form of the following reference:

In the text: "The results of this work have been obtained using the SaX package.[...]"

In references: "[...] L. Martin-Samos, G. Bussi, Comp. Phys. Comm. 180, 1419 (2009) 
http://www.sax-project.org"

We also encourage the users of SaX to publish in the form of supplementary materials
or on their personal web-sites everything needed to reproduce their
results, such as input files and eventually modified parts of the source code.

